---
/**
 * storage-engines · storage-engines-fundamentals · Figure 3 — Level 2, a B-tree
 * leaf split pushing a separator up to the parent.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source page (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). References marker-end="url(#arw)", so the grey #arw marker is
 * inlined here in a local <defs> (verbatim from the source defs block) so it
 * resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 540 170"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A B-tree split: a full leaf divides into two half-full pages and pushes a separator key up to the parent"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="270"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">INSERT into a full leaf → SPLIT</text
            >
            <!-- before -->
            <rect x="20" y="40" width="180" height="34" rx="6" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text x="110" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#7a2218"
                >[10 20 30 40] ← full, no room</text
            >
            <text x="110" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f">before</text>
            <line x1="210" y1="57" x2="252" y2="57" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <!-- after: parent gains separator -->
            <rect x="312" y="34" width="80" height="26" rx="6" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="352"
                y="51"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                fill="#7a1f12"
                font-weight="700">parent +30</text
            >
            <rect x="266" y="92" width="86" height="28" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="309" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e">[10 20]</text>
            <rect x="362" y="92" width="86" height="28" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="405" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e">[30 40]</text>
            <line x1="338" y1="60" x2="309" y2="90" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="366" y1="60" x2="405" y2="90" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="357" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >two half-full pages; split propagates up only if the parent is also full</text
            >
            <text x="357" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >danger: torn write mid-split → WAL replays it (full-page image / doublewrite)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Branching factor ~hundreds → depth ~4 levels addresses billions of keys. Writes overwrite a
        page in place; the WAL makes that crash-safe.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
